<!--  

The text below should appear as described; bold text, then underlined, then
both bold and underlined.

The text should not be clipped at the right edge. It displays first with
the width computed by the compiler.

When you click the button, the viewsystem sets the text view's width
to the computed runtime width, and the text display should remain
unchanged.

A bug [#493] in the viewsystem runtime currently causes a single pixel
on the right to be clipped when the button is pressed.

-->

<canvas> 
    <splash/>

    <window title="Fonts are fun!" width="400" height="400" resizable="true">
	<text>clicking the button should not change the width of the text field below</text>
    <button text="updateit" onclick="bu.measureDirty=true;bu.setWidth( bu.getTextWidth() );" />
    <simplelayout axis="y" spacing="10" />

    <text bgcolor="#ffcccc" id="bu"><b> Bold </b><u> Underline <b> Bold Underline</b></u></text> 
<!--    <text id="bu2"><b>Bold</b> <u>Underline <b>Bold Underline</b></u></text>  -->

    </window>
</canvas>

